    "This divergence in user preferences highlights the balance between user agency (the control they maintain over decisions) and the automation of processes.",
    "In future studies, we could explore how different levels of agency and automation affect task performance and user satisfaction [32].",
    "Additionally, users may require different levels of assistance in terms of breadth and depth.",
    "We could conduct further qualitative experiments to test the differences in decision-making paths when experts in visualization are assisted by agents [73], [74], comparing these paths visually using graph algorithms.",
